{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__001__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 1, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.1", "chinese_text": "常棣之華，鄂不韡韡。凡今之人，莫如兄弟。", "translation_ref": "常棣.1", "translation_text": "The flowers of the cherry tree --\nAre they not gorgeously displayed?\nOf all the men in the world\nThere are none equal to brothers."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__002__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 2, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.2", "chinese_text": "死喪之威，兄弟孔懷。原隰裒矣，兄弟求矣。", "translation_ref": "常棣.2", "translation_text": "On the dreaded occasions of death and burial,\nIt is brothers who greatly sympathize.\nWhen fugitives are collected on the heights and low grounds,\nThey are brothers who will seek one another out."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__003__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 3, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.3", "chinese_text": "脊令在原，兄弟急難。每有良朋，況也永歎。", "translation_ref": "常棣.3", "translation_text": "There is the wagtail on the level height; --\nWhen brothers are in urgent difficulties,\nFriends, though they may be good,\nWill only heave long sighs."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__004__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 4, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.4", "chinese_text": "兄弟鬩于牆，外禦其務。每有良朋，蒸也無戎。", "translation_ref": "常棣.4", "translation_text": "Brothers may quarrel inside the walls,\nBut they will oppose insult from without,\nWhen friends, however good they may be,\nWill not afford help."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__005__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 5, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.5", "chinese_text": "喪亂既平，既安且寧。雖有兄弟，不如友生。", "translation_ref": "常棣.5", "translation_text": "When death and disorder are past,\nAnd there are tranquillity and rest;\nAlthough they have brothers,\nSome reckon them not equal to friends."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__006__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 6, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.6", "chinese_text": "儐爾籩豆，飲酒之飫。兄弟既具，和樂且孺。", "translation_ref": "常棣.6", "translation_text": "Your dishes may be set in array,\nAnd you may drink to satiety;\nBut it is when your brothers are all present,\nThat you are harmonious and happy, with child-like joy."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__007__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 7, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.7", "chinese_text": "妻子好合，如鼓瑟琴。兄弟既翕，和樂且湛。", "translation_ref": "常棣.7", "translation_text": "Loving union with wife and children\nIs like the music of lutes;\nBut it is the accord of brothers\nWhich makes the harmony and happiness lasting."}
{"alignment_id": "shijing__xiaoya-luming-004__008__zhwikisource-20260530__legge-sheking-1871-ocr", "work_id": "shijing", "section_id": "xiaoya-luming-004", "alignment_type": "exact_or_near_exact", "confidence": 0.99, "order": 8, "section_unit": "poem", "segment_type": "stanza", "alignment_granularity": "stanza", "is_coarse_alignment": false, "coarse_alignment_reason": null, "source_segment_count": 1, "target_segment_count": 1, "chinese_ref": "詩經·小雅·鹿鳴之什·004.8", "chinese_text": "宜爾室家，樂爾妻孥。是究是圖，亶其然乎。", "translation_ref": "常棣.8", "translation_text": "For the ordering of your family,\nFor your joy in your wife and children,\nExamine this and study it; --\nWill you not find that it is truly so?"}
